 supercooled regimes. Moreover,\nthe effective barrier height increases almost linearly with the growing\ncooperativity length scale. An alternative calculation of the collective\nelastic barrier based on a literal continuum mechanics approach is shown to\nresult in very little change of the theoretical results for bulk properties,\nbut leads to a much smaller and less temperature-sensitive cooperativity length\nscale.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Jun 2018 03:14:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-06-15"}
